  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\n\r\nCurrently, there is a lot of code duplication in the `execute_transaction` functions.\r\n\r\n- [Frontier](https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/blob/9df7a3d02bc8a1a2d898d010c63ab7d567950d19/evm/vm/forks/frontier/vm_state.py#L45-L185)\r\n- [Sharding](https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/blob/sharding/evm/vm/forks/sharding/vm_state.py#L49-L184)\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\nA basic abstraction for the `execute_transaction` functionality. \r\n\r\nThe functions are currently divided into 3 distinct logical sections.  It would be pretty straight forward to create a class which implements hooks for each of these sections.\r\n\r\n```python\r\nclass BaseTransactionExecution:\r\n    def __call__(self, vm_state, transaction):\r\n        message = self.run_pre_computation(vm_state, transaction)\r\n        computation = self.run_computation(vm_state, message)\r\n        return self.run_post_computation(vm_state, computation)\r\n\r\n    def run_pre_computation(vm_state, transaction):\r\n        raise NotImplementedError(...)\r\n\r\n    def self.run_computation(vm_state, message):\r\n        raise NotImplementedError(...)\r\n\r\n    def run_post_computation(vm_state, computation):\r\n        raise NotImplementedError(...)\r\n```\r\n",
